          "name": "setDesc",
          "source": "Force a re-scan of the automations folder (otherwise scans happen on vault changes).",
          "target": "强制重新扫描自动化文件夹（否则仅在保险库内容变更时扫描）。"
        },
        {
          "type": "CallExpression",
          "name": "setDesc",
          "source": "Write a hello-world automation file plus an AUTOMATION-DOCS.md reference (every option explained) into the folder above.",
          "target": "在上方文件夹中写入一个 hello-world 自动化文件以及一份 AUTOMATION-DOCS.md 参考文档（解释每个选项）。"
        },
        {
          "type": "CallExpression",
          "name": "setDesc",
          "source": "When an automation-spawned session's process exits, close its tab automatically so tabs don't pile up.",
          "target": "当自动化生成的会话进程退出时，自动关闭其标签页，以防标签页堆积。"
        },
        {
          "type": "CallExpression",
          "name": "setDesc",
          "source": "Close an automation tab once its CLI goes quiet after the prompt ran (the AI finished its turn), even if the process stays alive. Off by default — a long task that pauses output beyond the idle timeout could be closed early.",
          "target": "当自动化标签页的命令行在提示运行后（即 AI 完成其回合）变得安静时，即使进程仍在运行，也关闭该标签页。默认关闭——长时间任务如果输出暂停超过空闲超时时间，可能会被提前关闭。"
        },
        {
          "type": "CallExpression",
          "name": "setDesc",
          "source": "How long a CLI must stay quiet before a session counts as finished — turns the tab dot gray and triggers the idle auto-close above. Default 10.",
          "target": "命令行必须保持安静多长时间，会话才会被视为已完成——这会将标签页点变为灰色并触发上述空闲自动关闭。默认值为 10。"
        },
        {
          "type": "CallExpression",
          "name": "setDesc",
          "source": "Path to the node binary used by the proxy. Leave as 'auto' for automatic detection.",
          "target": "代理使用的 node 二进制文件路径。保留为 'auto' 以自动检测。"
        },
        {
          "type": "CallExpression",
          "name": "setDesc",
          "source": "Print the proxy's diagnostic messages (node-pty / python bridge / pipe fallback) in the terminal. Off by default — these are normal fallback notes, not errors. Real launch failures are always shown. Takes effect on the next session start.",
